x4freetext: Three proportional counters (PC)
filled with 0.1 atm CO2 served as the dE detector.
A 1 mm thick 200 mm2 area silicon detector was the
stopping (E) detector.
The neutron flux was continuously monitored by a
50 mm2 area silicon detector placed directly below the
position of the 6Li or 9Be target.
Absolute differential cross sections were obtained by
comparison with neutron-proton elastic scattering from
a 9.7 mg/cm2 thick polyethylene target placed inside
the counter telescope.
Data corrected for background and finite geometry
Statistical uncertainties read from large
curves provided by E. Rosario-Garcia.
Approved by author 1977/02/11
Data taken from private comm., Rosario-Garcia,
1976/10. Data are presented in pdf-files.

x4freetext: Each of several 6Li targets was
prepared by evaporating a weighed quantity of lithium
metal enriched to 95% in 6Li from a tantalum boat onto
a 0.025 cm thick and 2.33 cm diameter tantalum disc.
The target thicknesses varied from 0.9 to 1.7 mg/cm2.
